net.sf.jclec.mo.comparator.fcomparator

Class EpsilonDominanceComparator

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.sf.jclec.mo.comparator.fcomparator.MOFitnessComparator
      • net.sf.jclec.mo.comparator.fcomparator.ParetoComparator
        • net.sf.jclec.mo.comparator.fcomparator.EpsilonDominanceComparator
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.util.Comparator<net.sf.jclec.IFitness>

    public class EpsilonDominanceComparator
extends ParetoComparator
    Compare two MOFitness objects in terms of e-dominance. The fitness objects should implement the IHypercubeMOFitness interface.

    HISTORY:

    • (AR|JRR|SV, 1.0, March 2018) First release.

    Version:
    1.0
    Author:
    Aurora Ramirez (AR), Jose Raul Romero (JRR), Sebastian Ventura (SV)

    Knowledge Discovery and Intelligent Systems (KDIS) Research Group: http://www.uco.es/grupos/kdis

    See Also:
    ParetoComparator, IHypercubeMOFitness

    • Method Detail

      • compare

        public int compare(MOFitness mofitness0,
                   MOFitness mofitness1)
        Compare two fitness objects.

        Here, the criterion used to compare is the Pareto dominance.

        Here, the hypercube is extracted from the fitness object in order to check the e-dominance.

        Overrides:
        compare in class ParetoComparator
        Parameters:
        mofitness0 - First fitness.
        mofitness1 - Second fitness.
        Returns:
        Comparison result for the given fitness objects: 1 if the first fitness is better than second fitness, 0 if both are equivalent, -1 otherwise.
